    "question_id" : 3144610,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Cast one of the integers/both of the integer to float to force the operation to be done with floating point Math. Otherwise integer Math is always preferred. So:</p>\n\n<pre><code>1. double d = (double)5 / 20;\n2. double v = (double)5 / (double) 20;\n3. double v = 5 / (double) 20;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that casting the result won't do it. Because first division is done as per precedence rule.</p>\n\n<pre><code>double d = (double)(5 / 20); //produces 0.0\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I do not think there is any problem with casting as such you are thinking about.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1079434,
        "reputation" : 790,
        "user_id" : 1076840,
        "user_type" : "registered",
