  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3144610/integer-division-how-do-you-produce-a-double",
  "title" : "Integer division: How do you produce a double?",
  "body" : "<p>For this code block:</p>\n\n<pre><code>int num = 5;\nint denom = 7;\ndouble d = num / denom;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>the value of <code>d</code> is <code>0.0</code>. It can be forced to work by casting:</p>\n\n<pre><code>double d = ((double) num) / denom;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>But is there another way to get the correct <code>double</code> result? I don't like casting primitives, who knows what may happen.</p>\n"
}